    {
      "id": "flow-title",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 40,
      "y": 568,
      "width": 400,
      "height": 20,
      "text": "Request Flow: curl https://api.github.com (\"both\" mode)",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e"
    },
    {
      "id": "flow-steps",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 595,
      "width": 860,
      "height": 250,
      "text": "1. curl calls connect(140.82.112.35:443) inside cgroup\n   ↓\n2. cgroup/connect4 fires:\n   • LPM lookup 140.82.112.35 → FOUND in allowed_cidrs (DNS resolver pre-populated it)\n   • http_proxy_ips lookup → FOUND (github.com is a proxy host)\n   • Stash: sock_to_original_ip[cookie] = 140.82.112.35, sock_to_original_port[cookie] = 443\n   • Rewrite: ctx.user_ip4 = 127.0.0.1, ctx.user_port = 3128\n   • Emit: event(action=REDIRECT, layer=CONNECT4, comm=\"curl\")\n   ↓\n3. curl connects to 127.0.0.1:3128 (thinks it connected to GitHub)\n   ↓\n4. sockops fires: maps local src_port 50123 → cookie\n   ↓\n5. MITM Proxy accepts, reads peer src port 50123:\n   • src_port_to_sock[50123] → cookie\n   • sock_to_original_ip[cookie] → 140.82.112.35\n   • Connect to real dest, MITM the TLS, inspect HTTP request\n   • GitHub repo filter: is /repos/org/repo in allowedRepos? → ALLOW\n   ↓\n6. SSL uprobe (Phase 41): observes SSL_write plaintext → logs GET /repos/org/repo\n   ↓\n7. egress_skb: packet to 127.0.0.1 → localhost exempt → PASS (backstop not triggered)",
      "fontSize": 11,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e"
    },
    {
      "id": "legend-box",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 580,
      "y": 560,
